WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.569 --> 00:00:04.203
-President Trump is turning
on some of his closest allies

00:00:04.203 --> 00:00:07.073
while standing by the one
that pays him, Saudi Arabia.

00:00:07.073 --> 00:00:09.475
For more on this,
it's time for "A Closer Look."

00:00:09.475 --> 00:00:13.379
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:00:13.379 --> 00:00:16.583
Trump did a sit-down interview
with Fox News over the weekend,

00:00:16.583 --> 00:00:18.551
and in that interview,
he said some things

00:00:18.551 --> 00:00:21.053
that might technically
qualify as news.

00:00:21.053 --> 00:00:23.823
But one thing he said
that was news to nobody

00:00:23.823 --> 00:00:26.526
was when he described
his decision-making process

00:00:26.526 --> 00:00:29.495
and made clear
he doesn't really have one.

00:00:29.495 --> 00:00:32.531
-When you're sitting at the
desk, how do you make decisions?

00:00:32.531 --> 00:00:34.300
I mean,
do you agonize over them?

00:00:34.300 --> 00:00:36.502
Do you second-guess yourself?

00:00:36.502 --> 00:00:37.670
-I don't think about it.

00:00:37.670 --> 00:00:39.872
I don't think about
how I make them.

00:00:39.872 --> 00:00:42.474
-Yeah, yeah, we know.
[ Laughter ]

00:00:42.474 --> 00:00:45.545
It's one of the symptoms.

00:00:45.545 --> 00:00:49.615
I imagine Trump makes decisions
the same way Netflix's algorithm

00:00:49.615 --> 00:00:52.685
suggests something
totally random for you to watch.

00:00:52.685 --> 00:00:54.653
"Did you enjoy
the migrant caravan?

00:00:54.653 --> 00:00:56.923
Then you might also like
raking in Finland."

00:00:56.923 --> 00:00:58.858
[ Laughter ]

00:00:58.858 --> 00:01:01.561
So while there's no process
to Donald Trump's decision,

00:01:01.561 --> 00:01:04.631
there is one central operating
principle, and that's loyalty.

00:01:04.631 --> 00:01:06.832
Doesn't matter who you are
or how decorated you are,

00:01:06.832 --> 00:01:08.067
all Trump cares about

00:01:08.067 --> 00:01:10.269
is whether you are nice to him
or mean to him.

00:01:10.269 --> 00:01:13.339
That's why Trump attacked
retired Admiral William McRaven,

00:01:13.339 --> 00:01:15.374
a Navy S.E.A.L.
who oversaw the operation

00:01:15.374 --> 00:01:16.709
to kill Osama bin Laden.

00:01:16.709 --> 00:01:19.545
McRaven has criticized
Trump's attacks on the press,

00:01:19.545 --> 00:01:20.980
calling him
a threat to democracy,

00:01:20.980 --> 00:01:23.182
but when Trump was asked
about McRaven

00:01:23.182 --> 00:01:25.818
he falsely accused him of being
a Hillary Clinton supporter

00:01:25.818 --> 00:01:28.387
just because Hillary
had reportedly considered him

00:01:28.387 --> 00:01:30.923
as a possible running mate
in 2016.

00:01:30.923 --> 00:01:35.128
-Bill McRaven, retired admiral,
Navy S.E.A.L., 37 years,

00:01:35.128 --> 00:01:36.829
former head
of U.S. Special Operations --

00:01:36.829 --> 00:01:39.098
-Hillary Clinton fan.
-Special Operations --

00:01:39.098 --> 00:01:41.968
-Excuse me --
Hillary Clinton fan.

00:01:41.968 --> 00:01:44.871
-I'm so happy we have a
president who blurts stuff out

00:01:44.871 --> 00:01:47.840
like a "Price is Right"
audience member.

00:01:47.840 --> 00:01:50.610
"Hillary Clinton!
$1!"

00:01:50.610 --> 00:01:52.211
[ Laughter ]

00:01:52.211 --> 00:01:53.979
Trump has also tried
to weaponize

00:01:53.979 --> 00:01:56.348
the criminal justice system
against his political opponents.

00:01:56.348 --> 00:01:58.651
For the same reason
he attacked McRaven,

00:01:58.651 --> 00:02:01.020
he wants to punish them
for their disloyalty,

00:02:01.020 --> 00:02:02.755
and he's being egged on
by Fox News.

00:02:02.755 --> 00:02:04.257
Yesterday,
"The New York Times" reported

00:02:04.257 --> 00:02:06.759
that Trump wanted to order
the Justice Department

00:02:06.759 --> 00:02:08.694
to prosecute James Comey
and Hillary Clinton.

00:02:08.694 --> 00:02:11.564
Some of his more vocal
supporters stirred his anger,

00:02:11.564 --> 00:02:14.099
including the Fox News
commentator Jeanine Pirro,

00:02:14.099 --> 00:02:16.235
who has railed repeatedly
on her weekly show

00:02:16.235 --> 00:02:17.736
that the President
is being ill-served

00:02:17.736 --> 00:02:18.971
by the Justice Department.

00:02:18.971 --> 00:02:21.040
So not only is the President
a wannabe dictator

00:02:21.040 --> 00:02:22.875
who thinks
he can jail whoever he wants,

00:02:22.875 --> 00:02:25.311
he also genuinely believes

00:02:25.311 --> 00:02:28.314
all the insane stuff
he sees on Fox News.

00:02:28.314 --> 00:02:29.916
Trump probably
sits there all day,

00:02:29.916 --> 00:02:32.151
watching Fox
and shouting to his aides,

00:02:32.151 --> 00:02:34.787
"Prosecute Hillary!
Stop the caravan!

00:02:34.787 --> 00:02:37.390
And ask my doctor is Otezla
is right for me!"

00:02:37.390 --> 00:02:42.661
[ Laughter ]

00:02:42.661 --> 00:02:44.564
"Why can't I have Otezla?"

00:02:44.564 --> 00:02:46.065
[ Laughter ]

00:02:46.065 --> 00:02:48.400
Trump doesn't care that Hillary
didn't actually break any laws

00:02:48.400 --> 00:02:51.504
or that McRaven is Navy S.E.A.L.
and decorated military hero

00:02:51.504 --> 00:02:53.706
who led a mission to kill the
world's most wanted terrorist.

00:02:53.706 --> 00:02:56.309
All that matters to Trump
is whether you're loyal.

00:02:56.309 --> 00:02:57.844
And sure enough,
Trump is now questioning

00:02:57.844 --> 00:03:00.613
the loyalty of the man who was,
constitutionally speaking,

00:03:00.613 --> 00:03:04.050
closer to him than anyone else
in the federal government.

00:03:04.050 --> 00:03:06.586
-In recent weeks,
with his electoral prospects

00:03:06.586 --> 00:03:08.655
two years from now
much on his mind,

00:03:08.655 --> 00:03:11.089
Mr. Trump has focused
on the person

00:03:11.089 --> 00:03:14.527
who has most publicly
tethered his fortunes to him.

00:03:14.527 --> 00:03:16.729
In one conversation
after another,

00:03:16.729 --> 00:03:19.598
he has asked aides and advisers
a pointed question --

00:03:19.598 --> 00:03:21.200
"Is Mike Pence loyal?"

00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:24.103
-Damn.
Now he's questioning Mike Pence?

00:03:24.103 --> 00:03:25.404
How paranoid can you be?

00:03:25.404 --> 00:03:26.906
Mike Pence has spent two years

00:03:26.906 --> 00:03:29.909
doing everything he can
to suck up to Trump.

00:03:29.909 --> 00:03:33.345
I mean, he literally copies
Trump's physical mannerisms.

00:03:33.345 --> 00:03:35.214
Remember that time Trump
put his water bottle

00:03:35.214 --> 00:03:36.448
on the ground during a meeting

00:03:36.448 --> 00:03:38.751
and then Pence immediately
did the same thing?

00:03:38.751 --> 00:03:40.552
[ Laughter ]

00:03:40.552 --> 00:03:43.322
I mean, look at that --
Pence is like a pageant mom

00:03:43.322 --> 00:03:45.224
who's doing
his daughter's routine

00:03:45.224 --> 00:03:46.959
along with her
from the audience.

00:03:46.959 --> 00:03:49.495
"And clap, then spin,
then step, step, step,

00:03:49.495 --> 00:03:53.333
then jazz hands, jazz hands,
jazz hands.

00:03:53.333 --> 00:03:54.433
For Trump,
loyalty only goes one way,

00:03:54.433 --> 00:03:56.569
and there's no better
example of that

00:03:56.569 --> 00:03:58.171
than the man who's arguably
closer to Trump

00:03:58.171 --> 00:04:01.341
than anyone else in the world,
Fox News host Sean Hannity.

00:04:01.341 --> 00:04:03.643
Just to give you an idea of
how loyal Hannity is to Trump,

00:04:03.643 --> 00:04:05.178
it was reported a few months ago

00:04:05.178 --> 00:04:07.180
that Hannity
has Trump's direct phone line

00:04:07.180 --> 00:04:08.514
and they talk
multiple times a day,

00:04:08.514 --> 00:04:10.650
including after
the Fox News host

00:04:10.650 --> 00:04:13.118
wraps up taping his show
most weeknights.

00:04:13.118 --> 00:04:15.255
Can you imagine
that conversation?

00:04:15.255 --> 00:04:17.056
It's probably
the phone call version

00:04:17.056 --> 00:04:19.325
of two dogs
sniffing each other's butts.

00:04:19.325 --> 00:04:20.693
[ Laughter ]

00:04:20.693 --> 00:04:22.828
And everyone in the White House
knows it's happening,

00:04:22.828 --> 00:04:24.964
because Trump will walk around,
flaunting the fact

00:04:24.964 --> 00:04:26.465
that Hannity
calls him every day.

00:04:26.465 --> 00:04:29.868
White House staff are aware
that the calls happen

00:04:29.868 --> 00:04:33.072
